main event: A civilian observed two circular objects over Teaneck, New Jersey, on 11 April 1966.
interesting points: The objects were the size of a pea and maneuvered erratically,The objects initially appeared white and then turned dull red,The sighting lasted for approximately 7 minutes,The objects were first noticed while traveling on Route 4,The report concluded the sighting was probably an aircraft.
witness description: Mrs. [redacted], a 35-year-old housewife with fair reliability
